### isPrevailingIRSymbol() {#a4087f59537491f4741a8e8c1d95af38e}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="bool llvm::lto::LTO::GlobalResolution::isPrevailingIRSymbol () const"
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Returns true if module contains the prevailing definition and symbol is an IR symbol.

For example when module-level inline asm block is used, symbol can be prevailing in module but have no IR name.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/lto/lto-h/#l00459">459</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/lto/lto-h">LTO.h</a>.

### Partition {#a9fb7283c89b4c6aaa60ca90af64cf740}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>unsigned llvm::lto::LTO::GlobalResolution::Partition = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a0ba893e7dc00f439ef557e79f12e899fa88183b946cc5f0e8c96b2e66e1c74a7e">Unknown</a></>}>
This field keeps track of the partition number of this global.

The regular <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/lto/lto">LTO</a> object is partition 0, while each ThinLTO object has its own partition number from 1 onwards.

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/any">Any</a> global that is defined or used by more than one partition, or that is referenced externally, may not be internalized.

Partitions generally have a one-to-one correspondence with tasks, except that we use partition 0 for all parallel <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/lto/lto">LTO</a> code generation partitions. <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/any">Any</a> partitioning of the combined <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/lto/lto">LTO</a> object is done internally by the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/lto/lto">LTO</a> backend.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/lto/lto-h/#l00472">472</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/lto/lto-h">LTO.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
